soil!—when the poorest landsman has had fresh fruit to his daily hand, and 
broken the world’s fresh bread to my mouldy crusts—away, whole oceans away, 
from that young girl-wife I wedded past fifty, and sailed for Cape Horn the 
next day, leaving but one dent in my marriage pillow—wife? wife?—rather a 
widow with her husband alive! Aye, I widowed that poor girl when I married her, 
